    "Paul Sciarra cofounded photo-bookmarking site Pinterest in 2010 with Ben Silbermann and Evan Sharp and left the company in 2012.",
    "Sciarra held onto a roughly 8% slice of Pinterest, which went public on the New York Stock Exchange in April 2019, making him a billionaire.",
    "Since 2014, he has served as executive chairman of Joby Aviation, a venture capital-backed firm developing electric-powered air taxis.",
    "Sciarra met Silbermann while they were students at Yale University; they cofounded Cold Brew Labs and launched an iPhone app in 2008.",
    "Sciarra and his wife Jennifer signed on to the Giving Pledge in May 2019, promising to donate half their assets to charitable causes."
